Farewell to the old cinema Paradiso, the cities are interrupting historic halls
The cinematographic historical halls are closed in favor of Multiplex.
"A city without a cinema is as blind as a face without eyes."
The picture offered by director Giuseppe Tornator successfully documents what is happening in large Italian city centers, but also in rural towns.
The process of restricting cinemas, the birth of large multisales in the suburbs and the subsequent disappearance of monosales in the central zones of cities is one of the events that seem inevitable and irreversible, but it also has all the features of a true cultural crime.
"It's like losing a friend, a friend, with whom we shared a piece of the road and a lot of emotions," feels the director of New Cinema Paradiso, a film that won the Oscar to Tornator twenty years ago, and the grand prize of the jury in Cannes and Cannes.
The values obtained by Anec, the main association of operators, speak clearly: in the last five years, the doors of 316 cinemas of the traditional tip have closed, and the highest bill was paid mainly by the halls in the most important cities: about 10 mins in Florence, about 5 mins in Boer, about 6 mins in Florence, about 9 mins in Ne Milan.
Among the regions most affected by the closures is Emilia-Romagna with a loss of 82 cinemas, followed by Tuscany (44) and Lombardy (41).
And proof that the first responsible for their disappearance is the advent of multiplex, are these three Italian regions, which registered the highest number of new cinema multisales: 195 more screens in Lombardy in the last five years, 81 in both Tuscany and Emilia-Romagna.
"The Italian process has evolved irrationally," says Paolo Protti, President of Anecu, "it is useful to create new structures, but it would be necessary to guarantee that the existing ones will survive, because when one cinema in the city closes, not all its visitors are willing to move to multiplex.
Then let's not even talk about the inadequate grant to the fund for the benefit of the operators: the previous public debt is about 10 million euros.
