Interesting is the case of Bologna, the first Italian city to worry about closures and which decided to find a starting point by signing a protocol between the municipality and Anec, the first of its kind in Italy to protect and promote small cinemas both in the historical centers and in the suburbs.
Among the planned norms are steps of tax relief in favour of operators and benefits for the public in terms of mobility: spectators will be able to go to the restricted traffic zone and will have special prices to stop at and at some parking lots.
"I like this initiative," says Giuseppe Tornatore, "and I hope that other cities will follow the example of Bologna by introducing other measures."
